val data = sc.textFile("s3://ibmdemo/activitydata_2016/*/*/*/*")
case class A(id: Int,userName:String,eventType:String,eventDescr:String,eventDate:String,eventMillisRaw:Long,eventMillis:Long)
val df = data.map(l => {
    val s = l.split(",")
    A(s(0).toInt,s(1),s(2),s(3),s(4),s(5).toLong,s(5).toLong/1000/60/15)
})
df.toDF().createOrReplaceTempView("activity")

%sql select eventMillis,count(*) 
from activity a inner join users u on a.id=u.id 
where a.eventType='Sale' 
group by eventMillis
order by eventMillis asc

import org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.Vectors
import org.apache.spark.mllib.regression.LabeledPoint
import org.apache.spark.mllib.classification.{NaiveBayes, NaiveBayesModel}

val res = sqlContext.sql("select * from activity a inner join users u on a.id=u.id where a.eventType='Sale'")
val products = res.rdd.map(l => l(3)).distinct.collect
val genders = Array("Male", "Female")
sc.broadcast(genders)
sc.broadcast(products)
val train = res.rdd.map(l =>LabeledPoint(products.indexOf(l(3)), Vectors.dense(genders.indexOf(l(9)),l(10).toString.toDouble)))
val model = NaiveBayes.train(train, lambda = 1.0, modelType = "multinomial")

val res = sqlContext
            .sql("select eventDescr,gender,age,maxTemp from activity a inner join users u on a.id=u.id inner join weather w on w.day = weatherDate(eventMillisRaw) where a.eventType='Sale'")
val products = res.rdd.map(l => l(0)).distinct.collect
val genders = Array("Male", "Female")
sc.broadcast(genders)
sc.broadcast(products)
val train = res.rdd.map(l =>LabeledPoint(products.indexOf(l(0)), Vectors.dense(genders.indexOf(l(1)),l(2).toString.toDouble, l(3).toString.toDouble)))
val model = NaiveBayes.train(train, lambda = 1.0, modelType = "multinomial")
